[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3586596777","html_url":"https://github.com/mui/base-ui/issues/2990#issuecomment-3586596777","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/2990","id":3586596777,"node_id":"IC_kwDOLW-eZs7Vxx-p","user":{"login":"LouisCuvelier","id":34551650,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0NTUxNjUw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/34551650?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier","html_url":"https://github.com/LouisCuvelier","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LouisCuvelier/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-11-27T16:04:09Z","updated_at":"2025-11-27T16:04:09Z","body":"I'm facing the same kind of issue by defining an initial toast (type info) with `timeout: 0`. Then I update the same toast with `toastManager.update(toastId, { timeout: 5000 })`, but it never close.","author_association":"NONE","pin":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3586596777/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"minimized":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3742043774","html_url":"https://github.com/mui/base-ui/issues/2990#issuecomment-3742043774","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/2990","id":3742043774,"node_id":"IC_kwDOLW-eZs7fCw5-","user":{"login":"joncoronel","id":59675970,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5Njc1OTcw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/59675970?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel","html_url":"https://github.com/joncoronel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joncoronel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-01-13T05:35:34Z","updated_at":"2026-01-13T05:35:34Z","body":"I have had this same issue but the fix doesn't seem like it would help with my use case. I already shared this in the discord but will add it here as well since it's related.\n\nWith that bug fix, it requires one of the conditions to be met in order to reset the timeout. The one's relevant to my use case are the `!hasTimer` and `timeoutChanged`.\nThese are my 2 scenarios: \n\nScenario 1: Toast starts with timeout: 0, later updated to 5000. First update does reset the timeout (`timeoutChanged`=true, `!hasTimer`=true). Try to reset timeout again through a second update with the same 5000 timeout value but it fails (`timeoutChanged`=false,`!hasTimer`=false).\n\nScenario 2: Toast starts with timeout: 5000, run update to reset with timeout value of 5000. Reset always fails (`timeoutChanged`=false, `!hasTimer`=false). ","author_association":"NONE","pin":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3742043774/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"minimized":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3742255587","html_url":"https://github.com/mui/base-ui/issues/2990#issuecomment-3742255587","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/2990","id":3742255587,"node_id":"IC_kwDOLW-eZs7fDknj","user":{"login":"atomiks","id":22450188,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDUwMTg4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/22450188?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks","html_url":"https://github.com/atomiks","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/atomiks/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-01-13T06:36:25Z","updated_at":"2026-01-13T06:36:25Z","body":"@joncoronel so you want a timeout specified in `update()` that's the same to still cause a reschedule? I've added a fix to #3564 ","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","pin":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mui/base-ui/issues/comments/3742255587/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"minimized":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repo